	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The art itself is really, really nice. Sadly, as pointed before, you have to use a specific palette, as well as follow the color limitations.
<br />
<br />Also, the actual palette differs a bit on different TVs and even on emulators.
<br />
<br />By the way (I hope you won't object), here is a quick view of how the same image could look if following the color requirements -- the modification is minimal:
<br />
<br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/8ycv1.png" alt="Image" />
<br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/3doqc.png" alt="Image" />
<br />
<br />(Note: I ripped my palette from FCEUX, and that was probably a horrible decision)

		

